@mheon Thanks! I guess that means that there is no plan to switch to the structure which is currently in REST API documentation.
@jwhonce I see, that's what I've suspected, it was pretty confusing for me that the other endpoint uses "new" REST API, but since it's a bug it uses just "different" syntax.

I think this issue should stay opened then up until the documentation (or most likely swagger, as pointed out by @Luap99) is fixed.

EDIT:
[I've actually found another issue which basically touches the same topic, but tested in 3.4.2](https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/13092)
